{"n":"thing","p":[{"b":23,"e":"TOPOLOGY THINKS A RING IS STILL A RING EVEN IF IT'S
ALL STRETCHED OUT AND TWISTED UP.

AS LONG AS IT COULD STRETCH FROM ONE SHAPE
TO ANOTHER WITHOUT CROSSING ITSELF,
TOPOLOGY DOESN'T CARE!","s":[{"p":[0,0,0],"r":[0,0,0],"s":[0.003000002,0.003,0.003000002],"c":[1,1,1]}]}]}

{"n":"thing","p":[{"b":23,"e":"VESICA PISCIS

GEOMETRY CARES EXACTLY WHAT SHAPE
A VENN DIAGRAM IS.

HOW FAR DO YOU THINK TWO CIRCLES
SHOULD OVERLAP?

ONE ANSWER IS TO GO HALFWAY, 
SO THE CIRCLES INTERSECT EACH OTHER
IN THEIR MIDDLES.

THE SHAPE OF THE CENTER IS CALLED
"VESICA PISCIS" AND CAN BE FOUND IN
GEOMETRY, ART, AND ARCHITECTURE.","s":[{"p":[0,0,0],"r":[0,0,0],"s":[0.003000002,0.003,0.003000002],"c":[1,1,1]}]}]}

{"n":"thing","p":[{"b":23,"e":"REULEAUX TRIANGLE

WHEN THREE CIRCLES INTERSECT
EACH TOUCHING THE MIDDLE OF THE OTHER TWO,
THE CENTER IS A PRETTY COOL SHAPE
KNOWN AS THE REULEAUX TRIANGLE.

LIKE A CIRCLE, THIS SHAPE HAS 
THE SAME WIDTH IN EVERY DIRECTION.
IT CAN BE ROLLED BETWEEN TWO FLAT
SURFACES SMOOTHLY!","s":[{"p":[0,0,0],"r":[0,0,0],"s":[0.003000003,0.003,0.003000003],"c":[1,1,1]}]}]}

{"n":"thing","p":[{"b":23,"e":"THE INTERSECTION OF 4 SPHERES

REULEAUX TRIANGLE, BUT DOESN'T

MEISSNER TETRAHEDRON.

{"n":"thing","p":[{"b":23,"e":"

THINKS IT'S COOL TO SHRINK A SPHERE DOWN TO A POINT.

OR A THICK RING TO A LOOPED LINE,  OR A CUBE TO A SQUARE.

A SOLID SQUARE IS LIKE A SOLID CIRCLE, OR A LINE SEGMENT.
YOU JUST CAN'T SQUISH OUT EMPTY SPACES, SO A RING
CAN'T SHRINK TO A POINT, AND IF A SPHERE IS HOLLOW INSIDE,
YOU CAN'T SHRINK IT ALL THE WAY DOWN.","s":[{"p":[0,0,0],"r":[0,0,-9.338149E-08],"s":[0.003000002,0.003,0.003000001],"c":[1,1,1]}]}]}
